{{Expand English|U.S. Congressional staff edits to Wikipedia}}
'''美国国会职员的编辑'''，指部分由美国国会工作人员对维基百科进行的编写引起争议，特别是是维基百科早期到2006年中期这段时间。如马蒂·米汉、科尔曼、康拉德·伯恩斯，<ref>{{cite web
 |url=http://www.bozemandailychronicle.com/articles/2006/02/09/news/wikipedia.txt
 |title=Burns' office may have tampered with Wikipedia entry
 |publisher={{tsl|en|Bozeman Daily Chronicle}}
 |author=Williams, Walt
 |date=2007-01-01
 |accessdate=2007-02-13}}
</ref>和拜登的条目曾引起媒体的关注。<ref name="Ars">{{cite news
 | author = Nate Anderson
 | title = Congressional staffers edit boss's bio on Wikipedia
 | url = http://arstechnica.com/news.ars/post/20060130-6079.html
 | work = Ars Technica
 | date = January 30, 2006
 | accessdate = 2008-04-28
}} The activities documented included:
:* rewriting Norm Coleman's article to make more favorable, claimed to be "correcting errors"
:* removing from Conrad Burns' article quoted pejorative statements he had made, and replacing them with "glowing tributes" such as "the voice of the farmer"
:* removal of unfavorable information from Joe Biden's article
</ref>还有其它如基尔·库特耐特的条目编写则很少受到广泛报道。

一些政客让自己的员工删除维基百科上的不良信息（包括含贬义的语句，打破竞选承诺的相关内容），加上有利的信息或赞扬的语句，在对手的条目中加入不利的内容，或者用工作人员撰写的传记来更换条目中的部分内容或全部内容。<ref name="Ars"/>

